---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import RelatedTools from '../../../components/RelatedTools.astro';

// Tool metadata
const name = "Calorie Deficit Calculator";
const category = "health";
const tier = "Health & Fitness";

// On-page SEO metadata
const pageTitle =
  "Calorie Deficit Calculator - Free Daily Weight Loss Calorie Calculator";
const description =
  "Free calorie deficit calculator that finds your maintenance calories (TDEE) and a safe daily calorie deficit for weight loss. Works as a daily, weight loss, and maintenance calorie calculator in metric and imperial units.";
const canonicalUrl = "https://toolkify.com/tools/health/calorie-deficit";
const ogImage = "/og/calorie-deficit.png";
const keywords =
  "calorie deficit calculator, calorie deficit, what is a calorie deficit, calorie deficit calc, calorie deficit meals, what is calorie deficit, how to calculate calorie deficit, how to be in a calorie deficit, calorie calculator, maintenance calorie calculator, calorie calculator for weight loss, weight loss calorie calculator, calorie calculator to lose weight, treadmill calorie calculator, daily calorie calculator, walking calorie calculator, calorie calculator to gain weight, running calorie calculator";
---

<Layout 
  title={pageTitle}
  description={description}
  toolName={name}
  toolCategory={category}
  keywords={keywords}
  canonical={canonicalUrl}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  ogType="website"
  hideBanner={true}
>
  <!-- SEO JSON-LD Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "WebApplication",
      "name": "Calorie Deficit Calculator",
      "alternateName": "Daily Calorie & Weight Loss Calculator",
      "url": "https://toolkify.com/tools/health/calorie-deficit",
      "description": "Free calorie deficit calculator that works out your maintenance calories (TDEE) and a safe daily calorie deficit for weight loss, with body-fat adjustment, BMR/TDEE tracking, weight-loss projection timelines, macro splits, and medical safety floors.",
      "applicationCategory": "HealthApplication",
      "operatingSystem": "All",
      "browserRequirements": "Requires JavaScript. Requires HTML5.",
      "featureList": [
        "Calorie deficit calculator with safe daily deficit targets",
        "Maintenance calorie calculator (TDEE) and BMR estimate",
        "Calorie calculator for weight loss in metric (cm/kg) and imperial (ft-in/lb) units",
        "Weight-loss projection timeline to your goal weight",
        "Calorie calculator to gain weight with surplus targets",
        "Macro split breakdown for protein, carbs, and fat",
        "100% private, client-side calculations"
      ],
      "offers": {
        "@type": "Offer",
        "price": "0.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD"
      }
    }
  </script>

  <!-- FAQ JSON-LD Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" is:inline>
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is a calorie deficit?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A calorie deficit occurs when you consume fewer calories than your body burns over a given period of time. When your energy intake is less than your energy expenditure, your body is forced to use stored energy (such as body fat) for fuel, leading to weight loss.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What does calorie deficit mean?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Calorie deficit means there is a negative energy balance in your body. It means the calories you consume from food and drinks are fewer than the total calories your body expends to stay alive (Basal Metabolic Rate) and perform everyday physical activities.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is a calorie deficit calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>A calorie deficit calculator is an online tool designed to estimate your daily maintenance calories (TDEE) and determine a target calorie intake to help you lose weight. By entering your age, biological sex, height, weight, and activity level, the calculator determines how many calories you need to consume to create a safe energy deficit.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to set a calorie deficit calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To set a calorie deficit calculator, input your basic physical statistics: age, gender, height, and current weight. Select your daily physical activity level (from sedentary to extra active) to calculate your maintenance calories (TDEE). Finally, select your goal weight loss rate (e.g., mild, moderate, or aggressive deficit) to establish your target daily calorie intake.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to set a calorie deficit calculator free?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>You can access and set our calorie deficit calculator entirely for free online with no subscription, hidden fees, or account registration required. Simply enter your physical details and activity metrics directly on this page to get your free personalized weight loss calorie plan.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What should my calorie deficit be calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>According to health guidelines, your daily calorie deficit should typically be set between 250 and 750 calories. A moderate deficit of 500 calories per day is the recommended default, as it translates to a safe and sustainable weight loss rate of approximately 0.5 kg (1 lb) per week without causing excessive fatigue or muscle loss.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How many calories should I eat calorie deficit calculator?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>The number of calories you should eat depends on your personal maintenance calories (TDEE) and weight loss goals. A calorie deficit calculator estimates your daily burn and subtracts a deficit (usually 500 kcal) to give you a personalized daily calorie intake target. For safety, men should generally avoid eating below 1,500 kcal/day and women should avoid eating below 1,200 kcal/day.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to calculate calorie deficit?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To calculate a calorie deficit, you must first find your Total Daily Energy Expenditure (TDEE) by multiplying your Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR) by your physical activity multiplier. Once you have your TDEE, subtract your target daily calorie intake. For example, if your TDEE is 2,500 calories and you eat 2,000 calories, your daily calorie deficit is 500 calories.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to calculate your calorie deficit?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>You can calculate your calorie deficit by tracking your daily food intake and estimating your daily calorie burn. Subtract your average daily calorie intake from your TDEE. Alternatively, you can use our calculator by entering your weight, height, age, and activity level, and selecting your target weekly weight loss rate to let the tool calculate your deficit automatically.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to be in a calorie deficit?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To be in a calorie deficit, you must create a gap between the energy you consume and the energy you burn. You can achieve this by consuming fewer calories through smaller portions and lower-calorie, nutrient-dense foods (dietary restriction), increasing your daily physical activity through exercise and general movement (energy expenditure), or combining both approaches for the most sustainable results.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How to do a calorie deficit?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To do a calorie deficit effectively, start by calculating your daily maintenance calories. Focus on eating high-protein and high-fiber meals, which keep you satiated for longer. Track your portion sizes, reduce liquid calories, and incorporate regular physical activity such as strength training or walking. Recalculate your target every 3 to 5 kilograms lost to adjust for metabolic changes.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is my calorie deficit?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Your specific calorie deficit is the difference between your TDEE (maintenance calories) and your actual calorie intake. If your body requires 2,200 calories to maintain its weight and you consume 1,700 calories, your current calorie deficit is 500 calories per day.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much of a calorie deficit to lose weight?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>To lose weight at a safe, sustainable pace of 0.25 to 1.0 kg (0.5 to 2 lbs) per week, a calorie deficit of 250 to 1,000 calories per day is recommended. A deficit larger than 1,000 calories is generally not advised because it can lead to severe muscle loss, nutrient deficiencies, fatigue, and a slower metabolism.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "How much calorie deficit to lose weight?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>The amount of calorie deficit required to lose weight depends on your timeline and starting weight. A deficit of 500 calories per day is standard for losing about 0.5 kg (1 lb) per week. If you have less weight to lose, a smaller deficit of 250 calories is often better to preserve lean muscle, while those with a higher starting weight may safely sustain a larger deficit initially.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Can you build muscle in a calorie deficit?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>Yes, it is possible to build muscle in a calorie deficit, a process known as body recomposition. This is most common in beginners, individuals with higher body fat percentages, or those returning to training after a break. To build muscle while in a deficit, you must eat a high-protein diet (typically 1.6 to 2.2 grams of protein per kilogram of body weight) and perform regular progressive resistance training.</p>"
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Why am I not losing weight in a calorie deficit?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "<p>If you are not losing weight, you may not be in a true calorie deficit. Common reasons include underestimating portion sizes, not tracking oils, dressings, or liquid calories, or overestimating calories burned during exercise. Other factors include temporary water retention from new workouts, hormonal changes, or metabolic adaptation, which means you may need to recalculate your TDEE based on your new weight.</p>"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  </script>

  <section class="max-w-[1000px] w-full mx-auto px-4 py-3 sm:py-6 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:gap-4 animate-fade-in-up pb-16">
    <!-- Breadcrumb & Header -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[10px] font-semibold text-slate uppercase" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Tools</a>
        <span>/</span>
        <span class="text-brand-blue capitalize">{category}</span>
      </nav>
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center justify-between mt-0.5 gap-2">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
          <h1 class="font-display font-medium text-xl sm:text-2xl tracking-tight text-primary">
            {name}
          </h1>
          <span class="bg-surface-pricing-featured text-brand-blue text-[10px] py-0.5 px-2 rounded-full font-semibold uppercase whitespace-nowrap shrink-0">{tier}</span>
        </div>
        
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 flex-wrap">
          <button
            type="button"
            id="share-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="Share tool link"
          >
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M8.684 10.742l5.028-2.513m0 7.544l-5.028-2.513M18 8a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm-6 8a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0zm6 0a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z" />
            </svg>
            <span>Share</span>
          </button>

          <button
            type="button"
            id="how-it-works-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-primary rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="How calorie deficit calculator works"
          >
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M13 16h-1v-4h-1m1-4h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"></path>
            </svg>
            <span>How it works</span>
          </button>

          <button
            type="button"
            id="reset-btn"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold px-2.5 py-1 bg-canvas hover:bg-surface border border-hairline text-slate hover:text-brand-coral hover:border-brand-coral rounded-full transition-all cursor-pointer shadow-subtle"
            aria-label="Reset calculator inputs"
          >
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="w-3.5 h-3.5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 1121.21 7.89M9 11l3-3 3 3m-3-3v12"></path>
            </svg>
            <span>Reset</span>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>


    <!-- Workspace Container (Zero-Scroll Compact Layout) -->
    <div class="card-base p-4 sm:p-5 flex flex-col gap-4">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-5 items-stretch">
        
        <!-- Left Pane: Inputs -->
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3">
          <!-- Unit Toggle (Miro Pill Style) -->
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
            <label class="text-[11px] font-semibold text-charcoal">Measurement Unit</label>
            <div class="flex rounded-full bg-surface p-0.5 border border-hairline self-start">
              <button
                type="button"
                id="unit-metric-btn"
                class="text-[11px] px-4 py-1 rounded-full font-bold transition-all cursor-pointer text-slate"
              >
                Metric (cm/kg)
              </button>
              <button
                type="button"
                id="unit-imperial-btn"
                class="text-[11px] px-4 py-1 rounded-full font-bold transition-all cursor-pointer bg-primary text-canvas"
              >
                Imperial (ft-in/lb)
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Sex & Age Inputs -->
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-3">
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
              <label for="sex-select" class="text-[11px] font-semibold text-charcoal">Sex</label>
              <select
                id="sex-select"
                class="text-input py-1 text-xs h-8 cursor-pointer border border-hairline-strong bg-canvas"
                aria-label="Biological Sex Select"
              >
                <option value="male" selected>Male</option>
                <option value="female">Female</option>
                <option value="other">Other</option>
              </select>
            </div>
            <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
              <label for="age-input" class="text-[11px] font-semibold text-charcoal">Age</label>
              <div class="relative">
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="age-input"
                  min="15"
                  max="80"
                  value="30"
                  class="text-input py-1 text-xs font-mono h-8"
                  inputmode="numeric"
                />
                <span class="absolute right-2.5 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-[10px]">yrs</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Height Inputs -->
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
            <label class="text-[11px] font-semibold text-charcoal flex justify-between">
              <span>Height</span>
              <span id="height-label" class="font-mono text-stone font-semibold">5 ft 9 in</span>
            </label>

            <!-- Metric Height (CM) -->
            <div id="metric-height-container" class="flex items-center gap-2 hidden">
              <input
                type="range"
                id="height-metric-range"
                min="100"
                max="230"
                value="175"
                step="1"
                class="w-full cursor-pointer accent-brand-blue"
                aria-label="Height in Centimeters Slider"
              />
              <div class="relative w-20 shrink-0">
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="height-metric-input"
                  min="100"
                  max="230"
                  value="175"
                  class="text-input pr-7 py-1 text-xs text-center font-mono h-8"
                  inputmode="numeric"
                />
                <span class="absolute right-2 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-[10px]">cm</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Imperial Height (Feet + Inches) -->
            <div id="imperial-height-container" class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2">
              <div class="relative">
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="height-ft-input"
                  min="3"
                  max="7"
                  value="5"
                  class="text-input pr-6 py-1 text-xs text-center font-mono h-8"
                  inputmode="numeric"
                  placeholder="ft"
                  aria-label="Height feet"
                />
                <span class="absolute right-2.5 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-[10px]">ft</span>
              </div>
              <div class="relative">
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="height-in-input"
                  min="0"
                  max="11"
                  value="9"
                  class="text-input pr-6 py-1 text-xs text-center font-mono h-8"
                  inputmode="numeric"
                  placeholder="in"
                  aria-label="Height inches"
                />
                <span class="absolute right-2.5 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-[10px]">in</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Weight Inputs -->
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
            <label class="text-[11px] font-semibold text-charcoal flex justify-between">
              <span>Weight</span>
              <span id="weight-label" class="font-mono text-stone font-semibold">176 lb</span>
            </label>

            <!-- Metric Weight (KG) -->
            <div id="metric-weight-container" class="flex items-center gap-2 hidden">
              <input
                type="range"
                id="weight-metric-range"
                min="35"
                max="200"
                value="80"
                step="1"
                class="w-full cursor-pointer accent-brand-blue"
                aria-label="Weight in Kilograms Slider"
              />
              <div class="relative w-20 shrink-0">
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="weight-metric-input"
                  min="35"
                  max="200"
                  value="80"
                  class="text-input pr-7 py-1 text-xs text-center font-mono h-8"
                  inputmode="numeric"
                />
                <span class="absolute right-2 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-[10px]">kg</span>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Imperial Weight (LBS) -->
            <div id="imperial-weight-container" class="flex items-center gap-2">
              <input
                type="range"
                id="weight-lbs-range"
                min="80"
                max="450"
                value="176"
                step="1"
                class="w-full cursor-pointer accent-brand-blue"
                aria-label="Weight in Pounds Slider"
              />
              <div class="relative w-20 shrink-0">
                <input
                  type="number"
                  id="weight-lbs-input"
                  min="80"
                  max="450"
                  value="176"
                  class="text-input pr-7 py-1 text-xs text-center font-mono h-8"
                  inputmode="numeric"
                />
                <span class="absolute right-2 top-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 text-stone text-[10px]">lb</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <script type="text/javascript" is:inline>
            (function() {
              const savedUnit = localStorage.getItem("calorie-unit") || "imperial";
              if (savedUnit === "metric") {
                document.getElementById("metric-height-container")?.classList.remove("hidden");
                document.getElementById("imperial-height-container")?.classList.add("hidden");
                document.getElementById("metric-weight-container")?.classList.remove("hidden");
                document.getElementById("imperial-weight-container")?.classList.add("hidden");
                
                const metricBtn = document.getElementById("unit-metric-btn");
                const imperialBtn = document.getElementById("unit-imperial-btn");
                if (metricBtn && imperialBtn) {
                  metricBtn.classList.add("bg-primary", "text-canvas");
                  metricBtn.classList.remove("text-slate");
                  imperialBtn.classList.remove("bg-primary", "text-canvas");
                  imperialBtn.classList.add("text-slate");
                }
                const labelH = document.getElementById("height-label");
                if (labelH) labelH.textContent = "175 cm";
                const labelW = document.getElementById("weight-label");
                if (labelW) labelW.textContent = "80 kg";
                const targetWUnit = document.getElementById("targetweight-unit");
                if (targetWUnit) targetWUnit.textContent = "kg";
              }
            })();
          </script>

          <!-- Activity Level -->
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-1">
            <label for="activity-select" class="text-[11px] font-semibold text-charcoal">Activity Level</label>
            <select
              id="activity-select"
              class="text-input py-1 text-xs h-8 cursor-pointer border border-hairline-strong bg-canvas"
            >
              <option value="1.2">Sedentary (Little to no exercise)</option>
              <option value="1.375" selected>Lightly Active (Exercise 1-3 days/week)</option>
              <option value="1.55">Moderately Active (Exercise 3-5 days/week)</option>
              <option value="1.725">Very Active (Hard exercise 6-7 days/week)</option>
              <option value="1.9">Extra Active (Very intense physical job / twice-daily workouts)</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <!-- Target / Goal Tiers -->
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-1.5">
            <label class="text-[11px] font-semibold text-charcoal">Target Goal</label>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-2" id="goal-container">
              <button type="button" class="goal-btn p-2 border border-hairline rounded-lg text-left transition-all bg-canvas hover:bg-surface select-none relative" data-deficit="0">
                <span class="block text-xs font-bold text-primary">Maintain</span>
                <span class="block text-[9px] text-stone mt-0.5">TDEE level</span>
              </button>
              <button type="button" class="goal-btn p-2 border border-brand-blue/30 rounded-lg text-left transition-all bg-canvas hover:bg-surface select-none relative active" data-deficit="500">
                <span class="block text-xs font-bold text-primary">Moderate Deficit</span>
                <span class="block text-[9px] text-stone mt-0.5">~0.5 kg/week loss</span>
                <span class="absolute top-1.5 right-1.5 bg-success-accent text-canvas text-[8px] font-bold px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-full">Recommended</span>
              </button>
              <button type="button" class="goal-btn p-2 border border-hairline rounded-lg text-left transition-all bg-canvas hover:bg-surface select-none relative" data-deficit="250">
                <span class="block text-xs font-bold text-primary">Mild Deficit</span>
                <span class="block text-[9px] text-stone mt-0.5">~0.25 kg/week loss</span>
              </button>
              <button type="button" class="goal-btn p-2 border border-hairline rounded-lg text-left transition-all bg-canvas hover:bg-surface select-none relative" data-deficit="1000">
                <span class="block text-xs font-bold text-primary">Aggressive Deficit</span>
                <span class="block text-[9px] text-stone mt-0.5">~1.0 kg/week loss</span>
              </button>
              <button type="button" class="goal-btn p-2 border border-hairline rounded-lg text-left transition-all bg-canvas hover:bg-surface select-none relative" data-deficit="-250">
                <span class="block text-xs font-bold text-primary">Mild Surplus</span>
                <span class="block text-[9px] text-stone mt-0.5">~0.25 kg/week gain</span>
              </button>
              <button type="button" class="goal-btn p-2 border border-hairline rounded-lg text-left transition-all bg-canvas hover:bg-surface select-none relative" data-deficit="-500">
                <span class="block text-xs font-bold text-primary">Moderate Surplus</span>
                <span class="block text-[9px] text-stone mt-0.5">~0.5 kg/week gain</span>
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Advanced Options Collapsible -->
          <div class="border-t border-hairline-soft pt-2 mt-1">
            <button
              type="button"
              id="advanced-toggle-btn"
              class="w-full flex items-center justify-between text-[11px] font-bold text-slate hover:text-primary transition-all cursor-pointer py-1"
            >
              <span class="flex items-center gap-1">
                ⚙ Advanced Parameters (Body Fat %, Custom Target)
              </span>
              <svg
                id="advanced-chevron"
                xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-stone transition-transform duration-300"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2.5"
              >
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"></path>
              </svg>
            </button>

