        answer is simple: a calorie deficit means you consume fewer calories
        than your body burns in a day. When that happens, your body covers the
        gap by tapping into stored energy &mdash; mostly body fat &mdash; and
        you lose weight. Understanding <strong>what is calorie deficit</strong>
        is the single most important idea in fat loss, because no diet works
        without one. This tool turns that concept into concrete numbers so you
        always know whether you are eating at, above, or below your maintenance
